VarAttributes.CATDESC: Default time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS4 FPI/DES burst data begin-time; derived from burst packet time.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES epoch plus var
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS4 FPI/DES epoch plus var

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES epoch minus var
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: MMS4 FPI/DES epoch minus var

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES 32-bit vector of data-quality indicators at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Value of zero signifies no quality errors. For non-zero values: Bit-0 = manually flagged interval, Bit-1 = overcounting/saturation effects likely present in skymap, Bit-2 = reported spacecraft potential above 20V, Bit-3 = invalid/unavailable spacecraft potential, Bit-4 = significant (>25%) cold plasma (<10eV) component, Bit-5 = significant (>25%) hot plasma (>30keV) component, Bit-6 = high sonic Mach number (v/vth > 2.5), Bit-7 = low calculated density (n_DES < 0.05 cm^-3), Bit-8 = bentPipe magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-9 = srvy l2pre magnetic field used instead of brst l2pre magnetic field, Bit-10 = no internally generated photoelectron correction applied

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES compression lossless/lossy indicator at survey-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DES compression loss indicator, 0=lossless, 1=lossy

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES step table parity, this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI/DES alternates between two tables, designated "even" (0) and "odd" (1).

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) count at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase counts range over [0000, 5759] cnts.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase count indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES Del-Phi (obs spin-phase) angle at burst-start time
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Nominally, spin-phase angles range over [0, 360) deg.  Each count represents 1/16 deg of observatory spin-phase.  Zero spin-phase angle indicates obs +X-axis aligned with Sun.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES sector de-Spin P value, this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Records P-value used to de-spin this burst sky-map on board.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES electron pitch-angle distribution for "low" energies during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: low energy bin: 0 eV - 200 eV.  pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron pitch-angle distribution for "mid" energies during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: mid energy bin: 200 eV - 2 keV.  pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron pitch-angle distribution for "high" energies during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: high energy bin: 2 keV - 30 keV.  pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" +X_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to +X_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" -X_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to -X_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" +Y_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to +Y_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" -Y_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to -Y_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" +Z_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to +Z_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy spectrum "near" -Z_DSC during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed over DSC velocity-dirs closest to -Z_DSC, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy parallel spectrum 30 degrees parallel to B during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed within 30 degrees parallel bentPipe magnetic field.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy anti-parallel spectrum 30 degrees anti-parallel to B during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed within 30 degrees antiparallel to bentPipe magnetic field.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: ---> MMS4 FPI/DES electron energy perpendicular spectrum 60 degrees perpendicular to B during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Counts, summed within 60 degrees perpendicular to bentPipe magnetic field.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES omni-directional electron energy spectrum during this burst
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Differential energy flux, averaged (weighted by solid angle) over all look directions, by energy bin.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS FPI/DES pitch-bin index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: pitch-angle bins: pitch index=00 bins quasi-parallel to B, ..., pitch index=29 bins quasi-anti-parallel to B.  pitch-angle bin size: 6 deg.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS/FPI energy-bin index used in some types of outputs
VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: FPI operations nominally bin data from 64 energy filters into 32 pairwise energy bins, indexed 0-31.  Nominally, bins are indexed in increasing energy order.  See FPI docs for details.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: Estimated systematic error (positive or negative) in spin-plane bulk velocity (km/s) due to imperfect sensor suite flat-fielding. This can be subtracted from bulk velocity to obtain the corrected velocity vector.

VarAttributes.VAR_NOTES: The 3x3 matrix is represented as: Row1) Pxx Pxy Pxz, Row2) Pyx Pyy Pyz, Row3) Pzx Pzy Pzz. Note that Pij=Pji.

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES electron temperature tensor DBCS matrix during this burst

VarAttributes.CATDESC: MMS4 FPI/DES electron temperature tensor GSE matrix during this burst
